FIVE F-16S DELIVERED TO SINGAPORE

     Singapore took delivery this week of the first five of eight
F-16 fighters on order from the U.S.  The aircraft were ordered
in 1985 under a package that included training of 100 F-16
Singapore pilots at Luke Air Base, Arizona.  The three remaining
fighters will be delivered by the end of this month.
