January 18, 1990

XLR-132 TESTED FOR 100 SECONDS

     Aerojet TechSystems reports that it has completed ten tests
of its new XLR-132 high pressure, liquid rocket engine, which is
being developed for the Air Force to power a transfer stage which
will boost payloads from low Earth orbit into geosynchronous
orbit.

The longest test was l00 seconds.  The XLR-132 weights l36
pounds, has a thrust level of 3,750 pounds and employs a new
lightweight turbopump, which cuts fuel tank weight and improves
engine durability and efficiency, according to Aerojet.
