DEFENSE INDUSTRY REPORT via NewsNet
January 18, 1990

MARTIN SAYS NEW TADS/PNVS COATING WILL SAVE $27.9 MILLION

  Martin Marietta said last week that a new long-life optical
coating it has developed for the TADS/PNVS night vision system
for the Apache helicopter will save the Army $27.9 million in
maintenance and spare parts costs over three years.

The new hard carbon coating is designed to last the 20-plus years
life of the aircraft and night vision system. The previous
coating, thorium fluoride, protects the windows for three years.
The new coating will be applied to the 161 new TADS/PNVS systems
on order and to 584 previously delivered units when their
original lens coating wears out.
