ARMY WANTS LIQUID SUSTAINER FOR INTERCEPTOR

       The Army Strategic Defense Command plans to request
letters of interest Jan. 31 for a 51-month program to develop a
liquid propulsion sustainer for an advanced endoatmospheric
interceptor. The program will incorporate advanced liquid
propulsion technology.  Engine components to be evaluated are the
tankage, pressurization system, combustion chamber (including
nozzles) and scaling of advanced liquid (gel) propellant
technology to production size batches.  Contact: Vickie Binford.
