DEFENSE CLEANUP via NewsNet
JANUARY 19, 1996

Rust wins Hanford work

     Bechtel Hanford Inc. of Richland, Wash., awarded a $7.5 
million contract to Rust Federal Services of Golden, Colo., 
to provide waste disposal services at the Environmental 
Restoration Disposal Facility at the Energy Dept.'s Hanford 
(Wash.) site.
     The ERDF is a long, deep trench that will be the central 
landfill for large quantities of hazardous and mixed waste 
materials dug up or uncovered during Hanford 
environmental restoration work.
     Rust will begin work at the ERDF when construction is 
completed this summer.
     Bechtel is DOE's environmental restoration contractor at 
Hanford.
     Contact: Rick Dale, 509-372-9097.



