DEFENSE CLEANUP via NewsNet
JANUARY 19, 1996

Alaska forts seek lab

     The Directorate of Contracting at Fort Richardson, 
Alaska, needs a firm to provide laboratory analyses of water, 
wastewater, paint chips, asbestos and other mixtures from 
forts Richardson, Wainwright and Greely, Alaska.
     Sol. DAHC76-96-B-0002 is a 100% set-aside for small 
businesses. Requests for the bid package must be sent to 
HQS, USARAK, Directorate of Contracting, P.O. Box 5-
525 Fort Richardson, Alaska 99505-0525. Bids are due Feb. 
26.
     Contact: Shirley Lucas at 907-384-7105.



