JANUARY 19, 1996

General Atomics to buy MODAR

     General Atomics of San Diego, Calif., has acquired the 
assets of MODAR Inc. of Houston, a supercritical water 
oxidation technology company.
     Supercritical water oxidation is an environmental process 
that can destroy many types of hazardous waste. 
Development programs at MODAR and General Atomics 
are now examining different supercritical water oxidation 
approaches to destroy excess hazardous materials aboard 
Navy ships.
     Contact: Bill Davison, 619-455-2406.



