DEFENSE CLEANUP via NewsNet
JANUARY 19, 1996

Army spurned sludge burning

     The Army incinerated liquids from the Rocky Mountain 
Arsenal's Basin F, not sludge as reported in the Dec. 15, 
1995, issue of Defense Cleanup.
     The Army gathered the Denver site's Basin F sludge into 
a waste pile and capped it. Later, the Environmental 
Protection Agency urged the Army to thermally desorb 
contamination from the piled sludge and incinerate the off-
gas. However, the Army instead has proposed to landfill the 
material (Defense Cleanup, 11/17/95).



