JANUARY 19, 1996

Kaho'olawe effort delayed

     Difficulties coordinating all the players have delayed the 
solicitation for cleanup of Kaho'olawe Island in Hawaii.
     The Naval Facilities Engineering Command Pacific Div. 
expected to issue a draft solicitation last Nov. 30. Now the 
draft isn't likely to hit the streets until late this month or early 
next.
     Last year, the Navy transferred the island to the state. 
However, the Navy, which used the island as a bombing 
range for 50 years, must now restore it. But that involves 
coordinating several Navy organizations, state officials, 
representatives of native Hawaiians, the Air Force and the 
Army Corps of Engineers.
     Contact the contracting officer, Ken Teague, by phone at 
808-471-1694 or by fax at 808-474-4551.



