DOE seeks NDE partners

     The Energy Dept. is looking for new members for
the Iowa State University Center for Non-destructive
Evaluation (NDE). The DOE weapons complex has
significant programs in non-destructive evaluation and
needs improved technology and expertise in production
and research.
     The NDE center is an industry-directed cooperative
research program with access to industrially oriented
scientists and engineers and members assist the
development of improved technology transfer.
