U.K. BUDGET CUTS SPARE MINEHUNTER ACQUISITION

Despite crippling defense budget cuts for the next year, the
British government announced on Dec. 1 that it would be issuing
invitations to tender bids for up to seven Sandown class
minehunters for the Royal Navy. The U.K. currently has five such
minehunters in its fleet, all built by Vosper Thornycroft
Holdings plc. Vosper is also supplying three Sandown vessels to
the Royal Saudi Navy, the company reports.



