U.S., CHINESE FIRMS JOIN TO FORM NEW COMPANY

New Orleans-based Offshore Navigation Inc. and the Shanghai
Bureau of Marine Geological Survey have formed a company called
Shanghai East China Sea Navigation (SECSNAV). The company will
offer offshore navigation and positioning services in the East
China Sea. Offshore Navigation has provided seismic services in
the South China Sea since 1978 and is licensed to operate in
China. For more information on the new company, contact George
Roussel at 504/733-6790.



