TRIMBLE RECEIVES INTERPHASE MARINE PILOT GPS CONTRACT

Interphase Technologies Inc. on Nov. 18 announced its selection
of Trimble Navigation's SV6 series GPS engine and marine antenna
for the 1994 Interphase Marine Pilot GPS. The minimum value of
the Interphase purchase is $1.4 million, according to Trimble.
The low-cost multi-phase Marine Pilot GPS is used on
sportfishing, light commercial and recreational boats for
accurate navigation and position information.



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
