JANUARY 8, 1996

Base Closure Commission closes doors

     The Base Realignment and Closure Commission, 
feared by base commanders for years under the 
acronym BRAC, closed at the end of 1995. 
     BRAC was set up to reduce the number of 
military bases at a time when force levels decreased 
rapidly and the Pentagon had to shed excess 
overhead cost.
     Some in Congress predict a return of BRAC. 
Senate Armed Services ranking minority member 
Sam Nunn, D-Ga., says the military needs to close 
more bases if it wants to have money for 
modernization.




